let _markdown = "\n\n# Chr3D Command Line Interface\n\nChr3D provides a powerful command-line interface for analyzing 3D chromatin conformation data from ChIA-PET, HiChIP, and Hi-C experiments.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install chr3d\n```\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```bash\n# View all available commands\nchr3d --help\n\n# Run complete pipeline\nchr3d run --mode <chiapet|hichip|hic> [options]\n\n# Generate restriction sites\nchr3d generate-sites --genome /path/to/genome.fa --enzyme MboI\n```\n\n## Available Commands\n\n| Command          | Description                               |\n| ---------------- | ----------------------------------------- |\n| `run`            | Run complete analysis pipeline            |\n| `generate-sites` | Generate restriction site file for HiChIP |\n\n## Analysis Modes\n\nChr3D supports three analysis modes, each optimized for different experimental protocols:\n\n### [ChIA-PET Mode](./chiapet)\n\nFor Chromatin Interaction Analysis by Paired-End Tag sequencing data. Includes linker filtering, mapping, and loop calling with statistical significance testing.\n\n### [HiChIP Mode](./hichip)\n\nFor HiChIP (Hi-C + ChIP) data. Skips linker filtering (HiChIP doesn't use linkers), includes restriction fragment filtering, peak calling, and loop calling.\n\n### [Hi-C Mode](./hic)\n\nFor standard Hi-C data. Generates contact matrices at multiple resolutions using pairtools and cooler.\n\n## Global Options\n\n```bash\nchr3d [--version] [-v] [--log-file LOG_FILE] <command>\n```\n\n| Option          | Description           |\n| --------------- | --------------------- |\n| `--version`     | Show version number   |\n| `-v, --verbose` | Enable verbose output |\n| `--log-file`    | Write logs to file    |\n\n## Pipeline Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Chr3D Pipeline                               │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│  ChIA-PET:  FASTQ → Linker Filter → Map → Purify → Categorize   │\n│                    → Peak Call → Loop Call → Significance        │\n│                                                                  │\n│  HiChIP:    FASTQ → Map → Purify (restriction) → Categorize     │\n│                    → Peak Call → Loop Call → Significance        │\n│                                                                  │\n│  Hi-C:      FASTQ → Map → pairtools → cooler → Contact Matrix   │\n│                                                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Examples\n\n### ChIA-PET Analysis\n\n```bash\nchr3d run --mode chiapet \\\n    --fastq-r1 sample_R1.fastq.gz \\\n    --fastq-r2 sample_R2.fastq.gz \\\n    --genome-index /path/to/hg38.fa \\\n    --linker-a ACGCGATATCTTATCTGACT \\\n    --linker-b AGTCAGATAAGATATCGCGT \\\n    --output-dir ./output \\\n    --threads 8\n```\n\n### HiChIP Analysis\n\n```bash\nchr3d run --mode hichip \\\n    --fastq-r1 sample_R1.fastq.gz \\\n    --fastq-r2 sample_R2.fastq.gz \\\n    --genome-index /path/to/hg38.fa \\\n    --restriction-sites /path/to/hg38_MboI_sites.bed \\\n    --output-dir ./output \\\n    --threads 8\n```\n\n### Hi-C Analysis\n\n```bash\nchr3d run --mode hic \\\n    --fastq-r1 sample_R1.fastq.gz \\\n    --fastq-r2 sample_R2.fastq.gz \\\n    --genome-index /path/to/hg38.fa \\\n    --chrom-sizes /path/to/hg38.chrom.sizes \\\n    --output-dir ./output \\\n    --threads 8\n```\n\n## Output Files\n\nEach mode generates specific output files. See the individual mode documentation for details:\n\n* [ChIA-PET Output Files](./chiapet#output-files)\n* [HiChIP Output Files](./hichip#output-files)\n* [Hi-C Output Files](./hic#output-files)\n";
